cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.CG, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, which are typically covered in the arXiv CS sub-categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Graph Theory (cs.GT), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The focus on maximum matchings and the characterization of graphs for which L(G)=2l(G) suggest that cs.DM and cs.GT are the most likely sub-categories. The use of upper bounds and the algorithmic results suggest that cs.CC and cs.DS are also possible sub-categories. The mention of NP-completeness suggests that cs.CC is more likely than cs.DS. The mention of polynomial algorithms suggests that cs.CG is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
